    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>114. Memorandum From the Presidentʼs Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from">Kissinger</persName>) to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_NRM1" type="to">Nixon</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d114fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>ʼs Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 10, Presidentʼs Daily Briefs.
                        Top Secret; Sensitive. Sent for information. Tab A is not published.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d114fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> informed the President that
                        Major General <persName corresp="#p_GGYJ1">Gowon</persName>, Chairman of the
                        Supreme Military Council of Nigeria, had agreed to a 3-week period of
                        International Committee of the Red Cross (<gloss target="#t_ICRC1"
                            >ICRC</gloss>) daylight relief flights to Biafra. A reliable source
                        reported that he made the decision in the face of almost unanimous cabinet
                        opposition.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1969-09-04"
                        >September 4, 1969</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>Morning Briefing Items</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="d114-01" n="1" xml:id="d114-01"/>
                <p>[Omitted here is material unrelated to Nigeria.]</p>
                <pb facs="d114-02" n="2" xml:id="d114-02"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Nigeria/Biafra</hi>: General <persName corresp="#p_GGYJ1"
                        >Gowon</persName> of the Federal Military Government announced yesterday
                    that Nigeria has agreed to the <gloss target="#t_ICRC1">ICRC</gloss> proposal
                    for daylight relief flights to Biafra. The agreement is initially set for a
                    three-week period, however, its extension will be subject to further
                    negotiation.</p>
                <p>A reliable source has reported that <persName corresp="#p_GGYJ1"
                    >Gowon</persName>ʼs decision was made in the face of almost unanimous cabinet
                    opposition. <persName corresp="#p_GGYJ1">Gowon</persName> reasoned, however,
                    that Nigeriaʼs position in international opinion was the crucial factor.</p>
                <p>Attached at Tab A is the <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Presidential
                    briefing.</p>
            </div>
